<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-17T21:42:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-17T21:42:00-05:00" n="398" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/101</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SJH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Shea</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-17T22:00:00-04:42">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1917, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.19 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your cipher telegram of July 9, 3 p.m. I have the assurance of Minister
                            of Foreign Affairs that if ships mentioned come to Chile with regular
                            merchantmen papers and flying the flag of the United States they will
                            receive full protection of the Chilean Government. He gives it as his
                            opinion that the civil courts will have no jurisdiction. I feel
                            therefore that under all ordinary conditions the ships may come to these
                            ports with safety.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SJH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>